<item>
            <title>[SPARK-5656] NegativeArraySizeException in EigenValueDecomposition.symmetricEigs for large n and/or large k</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-5656</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Large values of n or k in EigenValueDecomposition.symmetricEigs will fail with a NegativeArraySizeException. Specifically, this occurs when 2*n*k &amp;gt; Integer.MAX_VALUE. These values are currently unchecked and allow for the array to be initialized to a value greater than Integer.MAX_VALUE. I have written the below &apos;require&apos; to fail this condition gracefully. I will submit a pull request. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;require(ncv * n.toLong &amp;lt; Integer.MAX_VALUE, &quot;Product of 2*k*n must be smaller than &quot; +&lt;br/&gt;
      s&quot;Integer.MAX_VALUE. Found required eigenvalues k = $k and matrix dimension n = $n&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Here is the exception that occurs from computeSVD with large k and/or n: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; java.lang.NegativeArraySizeException&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.spark.mllib.linalg.EigenValueDecomposition$.symmetricEigs(EigenValueDecomposition.scala:85)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.spark.mllib.linalg.distributed.RowMatrix.computeSVD(RowMatrix.scala:258)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.spark.mllib.linalg.distributed.RowMatrix.computeSVD(RowMatrix.scala:190)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
